<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
*plz post mature response don't flame*<P>I constantly see people bragging about how they are soo twinked and there caster has soo much mana i actually thought about this for a few 5 minutes worked out some numbers, and came to the conclusion amount of mana is not very important only the regen is. take for example my druid at 29 has 178wisdom which is fairly twinked he kills a mob and uses maybe 1/2 to 2/3 of his mana bar kiting a yellow aviak avocet in south kurana then i set and regen mana. i took off all my wisdom jewery and kited it i used more mana (bar length) but my down time was exact same. The only fesable situation where i figured more mana pool would be important is when fighting a single mob that takes every single bit of your mana, or if you go afk to study and come back and waist all your mana on mobs then go afk again or maybe a duel. I also thought about hitpoints in the same additude but realised there were more exceptions such as complete heal exception where tank 1 has 1800hp and gets a CH when he is at roughly a bub of health 360hp. and tank 2 who has 2700hp and gets a CH at a bub 540 hitpoints. CH#A does 1440 heal CH#2 does 2160. Plus many hitpoint buffs are AC buffs also so they have more warrant. <BR>After thinking about it for quite some time i scratched my Dark elf necro for an iksar one. all i got to say is wow.= my DE was 22 when i deleted him gave all his gear to my iksar was a huge difference in down time from post 20 when you get allure death my iksar is only at 165int and i have traded many slots where u sed to have int to AC/AGI/HP/dex iems which are cheaper :P Well anyway please post i love to see some responses.
</FONT>
