<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Yep, absolutely true manabar.<P>It is extremely rare that anyone grouping is forced to go from fom to oom in a single fight. And in those cases it is rare that it would have been catastrophic, usually someone else could have healed, or the mob could have been rooted or mezzed or whatever.<P>In fact, 50+ the game revolves around continuous pulling with mana roughly moving between 80 and 20. If people are fom something is usually wrong   <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"><P>Mana regen is everything. Having said that, doesnt mean you neglect wisdom or int since there are really no mana regen items   <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"> those that have health to mana spells should go for regen items big time though.<P>For solo classes mana pool is much more important though it has to be said. If you are oom you have to *run*, and that means you just wasted an awful lot of time.<P>--------------------<P>Elasto, 57 Cleric
