<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Regen of mana is more important. Some people say that Erudites make the best Necros since their base INT is so high. I happen to disagree. Iksars make the best for one reason, regeneration (HP), even though they are tied with Humans for the lowest starting base INT. Necros get HP to mana conversion spells, the first of them at 8th lvl. Before the Call of Bones spell (34th lvl), an Iksar can have the hp2mana spell on while sitting or medding the whole time and not lose any HP. The same cannot be said for the other Necro races that don't have regen. While standing the Iksar would lose hit points like the other races do while medding or sitting. So the Iksar could have the spell on at all times with less downtime than the other races. With that being said, who cares how big the pool is, the faster you regain it, the better.<P>Troy
</FONT>
