Actually Int/wis does matter greatly. The mana regen rate for all casters is the same, the only way they are enhanced is by Clarity or bard's mana songs or any other uber armor that has a similar effect. I play a mage and mana is everything to me since I have to rely heavily on nukes and my pet. Once your int gets to around 200 its best to take up mana+ items instead since over 200 every int point only adds 1 mana.<P>As for your example Manabar, it proves that the regen rate is always the same. With your 178wis you used 1/3 to 2/3, when you took off you wis items you said the bar went down further. What actually happened is that you used about the same mana to kill the bird, but with your mana pool being smaller, your mana bar went down further to show that.<BR>Your mana bar shows your full amount of mana.<P>Example - <BR>Say at 178 wis you have 1000 mana, at 89 wis you have 500 mana.<BR>If you used 200 mana to kill the bird it will show a greater lost of mana on your bar for the smaller mana pool.<P>The mana pool may not seem to make a difference at level 29, but once you get to 40+ and start fighting bigger mobs you will see the difference in having a big pool.<BR>Just imagine if you had 200wis now from the 178, you would probably being using 1/4 bar instead of 1/3-2/3 and be able to fight a few more times before having to med.<P>In the end though.. your med time will be the same whether in parts or in one long med, since you're using about the same amount of mana to kill the bird and the mana regen rate is always the same (unless you got a clarity or mana song going) =)<P>Hope that helps =)
</FONT>
