<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Both total mana and mana regen are important.<P>For run of the mill grouping(single blue after single blue pulls) mana regen is more important. you use alittle mana each time and hopefully regen most of it between pulls. The faster you regen mana the longer you can keep up a non-stop pulling pace.<P>But when things go wrong it's good to have a large mana pool. There's no time to med, or it's just not safe to sit. <P>Fighting in Karnors recently i've had both situations come up. Most of the night it's single pull after single pull and i cast 2 spells per pull, then med. Mana regen is what's important now. <BR>But then, wham! train incoming and it's a fight for our lives and we're all oom at te end of it. Here's where having that large mana pool comes in handy.
</FONT>
