A caster must have the largest mana pool he/she can muster up. <P>At lev 1, 1 int = 1 mana every level gives +.2 mana per INT.<P>So at lev 50 1 int=10 mana<P>Knowing this 1- srround lev 25 +int doesnt count for jack but +mana significantly enlarges the mana pool.<P>If you dont have any form of mana regen, a large mana pool is esential. <P>I have a twink kit I put together to start all my low lev casters out with. All total My noobs start with +165 mana. At lev 1 when I put on all the equipment I get an extra 3 bubs and some change. It looks like I lose a ton o mana but I'm enlargeing my mana pool and I have to med up the added mana.<P>What this allows me to do is kill about 3 more newbe mobs before haveing to med up.<P>As I approach lev 25 the +mana becomes less and less significant. I usually put my +int items on arround lev 28.<P>--------------------<P>Just gimme somthin to shoot.<BR>Zaphid
