<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Having a large mana pool is absolutely useless in an epic mob fight. Even if that extra 2 bbs can get you say 4 more spells (thats what I get with my mage, 4 more nukes) than another caster with no mana/int items but has say a 50% increase in mana regen speed, the second will have a huge anvantage.<P>Epic fight = 30 mns (example)<P>In one epic fight you nuke 100 times.<P>In 30 mins you get off an extra 4 nukes, because of extra mana.<P>In 30 mins the other guy gets off another 50 nukes because of his 50% increase in mana regen.<P>So all that mana increaases your output by 4%, while a small mana regen increases his output by 50%<P>Therrefore, in an epic fight extra mana is useless. The same goes for a good group, you should never be at full mana in a good group. Heck, you shouldn't even get to fm in a BAD group.<P>In soloing, on the other hand, a large mana pool is great, since getting of an extra 4 nukes can easily save your butt while soloing. But I would still rather have more mana regen, since that would give me less downtime.<P>--------------------<P>True power does not exist, for I have not yet shown it to you...<BR>-----------------------------------<P>Long live Final Fantasy!<P> <IMG SRC="http://morty.50megs.com/nonflash/edgarversussabin.gif"> 
