<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
This argument is kinda silly because noone gets to choose between mana pool and mana regen on a day to day basis anyway.<P>If I could, it is interesting to wonder how much of a mana pool I'd give up to have, say, permanent self-clarity. I think it would be quite a lot.<P>In reality, we all have fixed mana regen and so we all just try to make our mana pool as big as possible with one exception really.<P>Any class that can convert hp to mana should try to make their hp regen as high as possible. In practice they will lose a tiny  amount of their mana pool to gain a respectable regen.<P>eg:<P>a shaman with iksar bp and Can III regens an extra 6 hp/tick, which is an extra 3 mana/tick, which is almost permanent breeze at the loss of at most about 10 wis (and his wis may be maxed anyway)<P>the same shaman with a fungi tunic regens 15 hp/tick or 7.5 mana/tick which is the same as permanent clarity<P>Hence, although I am on the side of the people that say that mana regen is all important, in practice I try to make my mana pool as big as possible since I cant affect my mana regen squat    <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"><P>(I know there are flowing thought items off the new Gods now, but I aint gonna see one of those any time soon    <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0">)<P>--------------------<P>Elasto, 57 Cleric
