<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Pulled from the castersrealm site.<P>Starting INT for Erudite INT casters, if maximum points are dropped into INT.<BR>142<BR>Softcap INT is 200.<P>Just looking at the levels and what it would mean.<P>lv1<BR>142=30mana<BR>200=42mana<BR>no big whoop, at least one more casting.<P>lv4<BR>142=121<BR>200=168<BR>Okay, that is 47mana.  That is quite a few spells.<P>lv8<BR>142=243<BR>200=336<BR>Okay, that is 93mana.  That is quite a bit for lvl8 spells...about 3 castings of some pretty nice damage.  Even nastier for some of the lower level stuff that you will still be using at this point.<P>lv12<BR>142=364<BR>200=140<BR>blahblahblah...same old stuff just better and bigger spells<P>lv16<BR>142=486<BR>200=672<BR>diff of 186<P>lv20 <BR>142=608<BR>200=840<P><BR>So, what does this prove.  Very simply, as has been stated, you can cast more spells.  This is much more important in groups that are pulling faster than you can regen.  You won't be OOM as fast, and thus will do better.<BR>As to the plus mana items...you must be joking.  What is a plus 10 mana to me at level 20...nothing...and the stuff with the uber plus to mana are Uber expensive.<P>Not saying that they aren't right about that at the lower levels...but, still takes just as long to regen.<P>Really, it isn't as important how much mana you have, but, as has been said, rather how fast you regen.<P>If you only had 200 mana, but regened that in 10 secs, you would be the god of the game.<P>--------------------<P>"Sleep is for the weak and those with slow internet connections" - Me
