<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I think the real point of this message isn't IS mana good to have but HOW good is it?  There are obvious advantages to a larger mana pool, when disaster strikes you have the ability to try to contain it because your reserves are deep enough to pull you through.<BR>  But at what point do you want to start making sacrifices in the area of pure mana and obtain other advantages?  For example hitpoints, how much mana is the ability to take an extra hit or two worth?  Same for AC or resists.  <BR>   Most likely as you play you will notice that you rarely drop below a certain amount of mana.  That reserve could be sacrificed to AC, HP or Resist gear.  I have an idea of about what I need to function, figuring that if I needed any mana beyond that and a reasonable reserve the fight was unwinnable anyway.  Once that level is achieved all the other desires could be concentrated on.
</FONT>
