<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Your mana pool should be as large as you can get it. Period. It's the difference between that extra one, two, maybe even three complete heals for a cleric. It's several extra mez's from the chanters. It's being able to do the exact same casting as a druid and still have mana left for an evac if needed. You'll never get that extra ice comet off if the mana isn't there. <P>For soloing for druids it's being able to quad kite higher level mobs because you have enough mana to actually kill them all. For Necros it makes the difference by 4 to 5 levels of what mob you're killing post 50. you simply have to have the mana to re-apply dots as they wear off. <P>If you die in the fight because everyone is oom, then you'll get your mana back realy fast. I'd rather wait on it personaly.<P>--------------------<P>Aazamn <BR>54th lvl Heretical Erudite of Prexus<BR>"The best way to ensure that you satisfy no one, is to try to satisfy everyone." - unknown
