Having more mana doesn't slow down the rate at which you get it back. Just because my car has a bigger gas tank than yours doesn't mean that the fuel from the pump goes into my car slower. It takes longer to fill my car up, yes. I am getting my gas just as quickly as you though. But I can now drive further, for a longer duration, if need be. <P>If you are burning all your mana in every fight as an int caster in a group, the camp is at the very edge of your group's abilities. If you are getting hit regularly as an int caster (with the exception of the occasional beating the chanters get), and therefore need to invest in ac, agil, or hp gear, then you are a problem for your group. You are not managing agro well, and that will get everyone killed. You need to lay off the nukes and settle back a little.<P>--------------------<P>Aazamn <BR>54th lvl Heretical Erudite of Prexus<BR>"The best way to ensure that you satisfy no one, is to try to satisfy everyone." - unknown
