Umm.. not sure where that analogy is heading really. Let me put my point another way.<P>Basically, at my lvl the group pulls continously unless either I, or the enchanter are lom.<P>Eventually, we pull at a rate such that my mana hovers at between 80 and 40. If they pull too much too quick, we have to kill a bit slower for a bit while I catch up.<P>Medding at lvl 50 gives you 25 mana per tick. Clarity 2 adds 11 mana per tick, almost a 50% increase.<P>Over the long haul, the only thing that is determining the rate at which the group kills is the rate I regen mana at (if anyone else is oom and I am not, the group tells them to med and pulls anyway   <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0">)<P>With Clarity 2, using the same tactics, we can kill 50% more mobs over any given period of time.<P>So how much wisdom would I give up to gain a 50% increase in xp and loot over a given period of time? Dunno, but I wish I was given the option   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>And, err, yeah, if a warrior could wear a regen item that gave him a *significant* amount of regen, say a bp that gave 50 pts per tick but had no ac, I'd say that would be worth wearing for xp grinds too.<P>--------------------<P>Elasto, 57 Cleric
